    "content": "**Geopolitiks Snacks** — April 13, 2026\n\n---\n\n## ⛴️ The US Just Blockaded Iran. The UK and France Are Not On Board.\n\nAfter peace talks in Pakistan collapsed this weekend, the US began a full naval blockade of Iranian ports in the Strait of Hormuz at 10 a.m. ET today — and threatened to sink Iranian ships that come near it.\n\n- **What happened:** Peace talks broke down over Iran's alleged nuclear ambitions. Trump announced the blockade Sunday, it took effect Monday. Oil topped $100/barrel again. US Central Command says the blockade applies to all vessels entering or leaving Iranian ports — but not to non-Iranian traffic through the strait.\n- **Europe's response:** Emmanuel Macron announced France and the UK will convene talks to \"restore freedom of navigation.\" UK PM Keir Starmer said the UK is \"not supporting a blockade.\" The Western coalition just split publicly over the most consequential US military action in the region in years.\n\n*The US declared a naval blockade of a sovereign nation and the UK said no. Europe said no. Oil said $100.*\n\n**Sources:** [CNN](https://edition.cnn.com/2026/04/13/world/live-news/iran-us-war-trump-hormuz) | [CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/04/13/trump-iran-war-strait-of-hormuz-blockade.html) | [NPR](https://www.npr.org/2026/04/12/nx-s1-5782538/u-s-iran-peace-talks-islamabad-collapse) | [Al Jazeera](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/liveblog/2026/4/13/iran-war-live-us-military-to-block-iranian-port-traffic-in-hormuz-strait)\n\n---\n\n## 🗳️ Orbán Lost. Magyar Won a Supermajority. The EU Is Thrilled.\n\nResults are in from Sunday's Hungarian election: Péter Magyar's Tisza Party won 138 of 199 parliamentary seats on 53.6% of the vote — a supermajority. Viktor Orbán conceded and is out after 16 years.\n\n- **What this means structurally:** Tisza has enough seats to amend Hungary's Constitution — the same one Orbán spent 16 years rewriting. Record turnout of ~79%. The EU immediately announced this could unblock a €90 billion loan to Ukraine that Orbán had been vetoing.\n- **The coalition that endorsed the loser:** J.D. Vance flew to Budapest to personally endorse Orbán last week. Vladimir Putin's support was public. The candidate backed by the US Vice President and the Russian President lost by 16 points.\n\n*The man with US MAGA endorsement and Russian backing lost by 16 points. Voters had opinions.*\n\n**Sources:** [CNN](https://www.cnn.com/2026/04/12/world/live-news/hungary-election-orban-magyar) | [Al Jazeera](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/4/12/hungary-election-early-results-show-magyars-tisza-ahead-of-orbans-fidesz) | [CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/04/12/hungarians-vote-in-closely-watched-landmark-election-.html)\n\n---\n\n## 💸 The Iran War Now Has a Food Inflation Subplot\n\nThe UN's Food and Agriculture Organization warned that the Iran conflict is choking off oil, natural gas, urea, and fertilizer from global markets — and that continued disruption risks serious food price inflation worldwide.\n\n- **The mechanism:** Hormuz disruption → energy prices up → fertilizer production and shipping costs up → food prices up. The FAO's Chief Economist said a functioning ceasefire is \"essential\" to avoid the food inflation spiral.\n- **The tab so far:** EU fuel costs are up ~$16 billion since the conflict began. US CPI jumped from 2.4% in February to an estimated 3.4% in March. The blockade that started today is expected to push that further.\n\n*The US started a war about nuclear weapons, and the sequel is a food inflation crisis.*\n\n**Sources:** [Crestwood Advisors](https://www.crestwoodadvisors.com/april-2026-economic-and-market-update-geopolitics-at-the-forefront/) | [CNN Analysis](https://edition.cnn.com/2026/04/13/politics/trump-strait-blockade-hormuz-iran-war-analysis)"
  }
